Church located in the path area set back from the grand boulevards. The interior is baroque. The arrangement of chairs inside is atypical.  Also worth seeing are the immersion baptismal funds which are around twenty years old and located at the start of what was the central aisle. It is accessed by small steps. The grid which covers the whole thing is very beautiful and elaborate. Worth seeing.

We came here for a concert and not for a mass... The church is not too big and its acoustics are good. The arrangement of the chairs had been made in such a way that one could easily see and hear from all seats.

The church is worth a detour for its immersion baptistery: opposite the entrance under grilles.  The high altar is also interesting: it is literally a table. The monumental nativity scene is also worth a look. On the other hand, the church is not very well lit.
